STRINGBUILDER BUILT-IN METHODS :
append() → Adds text at the end of the string.
insert() → Inserts text at a specified index.
replace() → Replaces characters between given indexes.
delete() → Removes characters between given indexes.
reverse() → Reverses the string content.
length() → Returns the number of characters.
capacity() → Returns current storage capacity.
charAt() → Returns character at a specific index.
setCharAt() → Changes character at a specific index.
toString() → Converts StringBuilder to String.

STRINGBUFFER BUILT-IN METHODS :
append() → Adds text at the end of the string.
insert() → Inserts text at a specified index.
replace() → Replaces characters between given indexes.
delete() → Removes characters between given indexes.
reverse() → Reverses the string content.
length() → Returns the number of characters.
capacity() → Returns current storage capacity.
charAt() → Returns character at a specific index.
setCharAt() → Changes character at a specific index.
toString() → Converts StringBuffer to String.

Both have same methods.
KEY DIFFERENCES :
StringBuilder → Fast, not safe for multi-threading
StringBuffer → Safe for multi-threading, but slower
